xml: header, row++newline.
header: Label++SpacePattern, newline.
{ebb: Adding a newline at the end of this helped put a definite stop to the header!}
Label: ["A"-"z"]+, "."?.
-SpacePattern: newline, tab, newline.
-newline: -#d?, -#a.
-tab: -[#9].

row: name, separator, type, separator, category, separator, power, separator, accuracy, separator, pp, separator, effect.

{-separator: #9, #32?.}
-separator: #9.
{ebb: I simplified your separator. I wasn't sure what #32 was, and I think it's not actually in the document? Anyway, when 
I keep it, the grammar produces 32,000+ possible parses: it's pretty seriously ambiguous. When I use JUST the tab character as a separator,
this works fine with your grammar. }

{-newline: -#d?, -#a.}
{ebb: You had already defined this rule for a newline: once I commented the second one out, things worked fine!}

{ebb: I inserted semicolons as "or" statements in between the Unicode hexes for the rules below.}
name: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
type: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
category: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
power: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
accuracy: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
pp: ~[#9;#a;#d]+.
effect: ~[#a;#d]+.
